        "content": "<p>Thank you again all, for your responses. <br>\nI've been able to generate verified deductions (in this course's configuration) for all of the exercises for chapter 1 and have moved on to chapter 2 but am quickly reaching a point where, while I feel I can grasp the structure of the proof, I am not sure enough of the syntax to reflect the proof structure in the code environment. </p>\n<p>Previously, the proofs have followed a structure similar to classic two column proofs where the <code>:= by</code> serves to separate a claim from its justification. <br>\nNow that I can introduce intermediate steps, and multiple goals, the status of my open goals, and where <em>in the code</em> a relevant tactic must be invoked, is becoming increasingly unclear to me.</p>\n<p>More concretely, there are just some of the exercises where I feel like I hit a wall when it comes to producing the proof in lean, and I am not sure if it is a result of a gap in my understanding of the relevant mathematics, proof technique, or simply how to implement it in code. <span aria-label=\"sweat smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f605\" role=\"img\" title=\"sweat smile\">:sweat_smile:</span></p>\n<p>Maybe I just need a hint to get back on track. </p>\n<p>Here is one that has been vexing me for a while <span aria-label=\"sweat\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f613\" role=\"img\" title=\"sweat\">:sweat:</span> ; <br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/ahM6fxKCjUclA5czYSRHcnTM/image.png\">image.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/ahM6fxKCjUclA5czYSRHcnTM/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/3121/ahM6fxKCjUclA5czYSRHcnTM/image.png\"></a></div><p>All of my manual proofs keep getting stuck at deriving y = 1 /x</p>",
        "id": 439052177,
        "sender_full_name": "Adam Millar",
        "timestamp": 1715874869
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><del>I'm curious what h1 is supposed to be</del> I can't read</p>",
